=== Vocalic register ===
Unlike the surrounding Burmese and [[Thai language|Thai]] languages, Mon is not a [[tone (linguistics)|tonal language]].  As in many Mon<U+2013>Khmer languages, Mon uses a vowel-phonation or vowel-[[register (phonology)|register]] system in which the quality of voice in pronouncing the vowel is phonemic.  There are two registers in Mon:

#Clear (modal) voice, analyzed by various linguists as ranging from ordinary to [[Creaky voice|creaky]]
#[[Breathy voice]], vowels have a distinct breathy quality

In the examples below, breathy voice is marked with a grave accent.

==Syntax==
===Verbs and verb phrases===

Mon verbs do not inflect for person.  Tense is shown through particles.

Some verbs have a morphological causative (Pan Hla 1989:29):

{| class="wikitable"
|-
! Underived verb !! Gloss !! Causative verb !! Gloss
|-
| ch<U+0252>t || to die || k<U+0259>c<U+0252>t || to kill
|-
| l<U+025C>m || to be ruined || p<U+0259>l<U+0252>m || to destroy
|-
| kha<U+0268><U+014B> || to be firm|| p<U+0259>kha<U+0268><U+014B> ||to make firm
|-
| t<U+025B>m || to know || p<U+0259>t<U+025B>m || to inform
|}

===Nouns and noun phrases===
====Singular and Plural====

Mon nouns do not inflect for number.  That is, they do not have separate forms for singular and plural:

{| 
|-
|{{my|}}
|{{my|<U+1041>}}
|{{my|}}
|-
| s<U+0254>t pakaw
| m<U+00F2>a
| m<U+00E8>a
|-
| apple
| one
| classifier
|}
'one apple'

{| 
|-
|{{my|}}
|{{my|<U+1042>}}
|{{my|}}
|-
| s<U+0254>t pakaw
| <U+0253>a
| m<U+00E8>a
|-
| apple
| two
| classifier
|}
'two apples'

====Demonstratives====

Demonstratives follow the noun:

{|
|-
| <U+014B>oa || n<U+0254><U+0294>
|-
| day || this
|-
|colspan="2"|this day
|}

====Classifiers====

Like many other Southeast Asian languages, Mon has [[Classifier (linguistics)|classifiers]] which are used when a noun appears with a numeral.  The choice of classifier depends on the semantics of the noun involved.

{| class="wikitable" border="1"
|-
!IPA
|kaneh 	
|m<U+00F2>a 	
|tan<U+0259>ng
|-
!Gloss
|pen 	
|one 	
|classifier
|}
'one pen'

{| class="wikitable" border="1"
|-
!IPA
|chup 	
|m<U+00F2>a	
|tan<U+0252>m
|-
!Gloss
|tree	
|one	
|classifier
|}
'one tree'

===Prepositions and prepositional phrases===

Mon is a prepositional language.

{| 
|-
|  <U+0257>oa||<U+0259>ma
|-
| in || lake
|-
|'in the lake'
|}

